### protected-test-api - Device Flow Demo Collection
###
### Purpose:
### 1) Inspect hypermedia controls at API root
### 2) Explore RFC 9728 protected resource metadata discovery from a 401 challenge
### 3) Run OAuth device flow manually against auth-server
### 4) Call protected endpoint with the auth-server-issued bearer token
###
### Notes:
### - This file does NOT start app processes.
### - Start apps first:
###   - auth-server on http://localhost:9090
###   - protected-test-api on http://localhost:8082
### - Run requests in order.
###
### IntelliJ tip:
### - Response handler scripts in this file store values globally:
###   {{deviceCode}}, {{userCode}}, {{verificationUri}},
###   {{verificationUriComplete}}, {{accessToken}}, {{resourceMetadataUrl}}

@protectedApiUrl = http://localhost:8082
@brokerUrl = http://localhost:9090
@clientId = protected-test-api-hypermedia-client
@clientSecret = protected-test-api-secret
@scope = hypermedia.access

### 0) Negative Test (post-login) - No Token
### Should still return 401 + WWW-Authenticate including resource_metadata
GET {{protectedApiUrl}}/protected
Accept: application/json

### 1) Root Hypermedia (HAL-FORMS)
### Should include:
### - _links.profile -> /AGENTS.md
### - _links.authorization-server-metadata
### - _links.oauth-protected-resource-metadata
### - _templates.start-device-flow
GET {{protectedApiUrl}}/
Accept: application/prs.hal-forms+json


### 2) Agent Contract / Profile
GET {{protectedApiUrl}}/AGENTS.md
Accept: text/markdown


### 3) Auth Server Discovery Metadata
### Inspect token and device endpoints exposed by auth-server.
GET {{brokerUrl}}/.well-known/openid-configuration
Accept: application/json

### 3b) Protected Resource Metadata (RFC 9728)
GET {{protectedApiUrl}}/.well-known/oauth-protected-resource
Accept: application/json

### 3c) Trigger 401 challenge and extract resource_metadata URL
### Should return:
### - 401 Unauthorized
### - WWW-Authenticate: Bearer ... resource_metadata="..."
### - application/problem+json body with detail explaining next steps
# @name metadataChallenge
GET {{protectedApiUrl}}/protected
Accept: application/json

> {%
  const challenge =
    response.headers.valueOf("WWW-Authenticate")
    || response.headers.valueOf("www-authenticate")
    || "";

  client.global.set("wwwAuthenticate", challenge);
  const match = /resource_metadata="([^"]+)"/.exec(challenge);
  if (match) {
    client.global.set("resourceMetadataUrl", match[1]);
    client.log("resource_metadata extracted: " + match[1]);
  } else {
    client.log("resource_metadata not found in WWW-Authenticate: " + challenge);
  }
  client.log("problem detail: " + (response.body?.detail || "(missing)"));
%}

### 3d) Follow resource_metadata URL discovered from WWW-Authenticate
### If step 3c did not extract the variable, run 3c first.
GET {{resourceMetadataUrl}}
Accept: application/json


### 4) Start Device Authorization
### This returns device_code, user_code, verification_uri, verification_uri_complete.
### After running, open verification_uri_complete in browser and login/consent.
# @name startDeviceAuthorization
POST {{brokerUrl}}/oauth2/device_authorization
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
Accept: application/json

client_id={{clientId}}&client_secret={{clientSecret}}&scope={{scope}}

> {%
  client.global.set("deviceCode", response.body.device_code);
  client.global.set("userCode", response.body.user_code);
  client.global.set("verificationUri", response.body.verification_uri);
  client.global.set("verificationUriComplete", response.body.verification_uri_complete || "");
  client.global.set("pollInterval", response.body.interval || 5);

  client.log("device_code saved to {{deviceCode}}");
  client.log("user_code: " + response.body.user_code);
  client.log("verification_uri: " + response.body.verification_uri);
  client.log("verification_uri_complete: " + (response.body.verification_uri_complete || "(none)"));
%}


### 5) Poll Token Endpoint (rerun this request manually)
### Before browser approval, response is usually:
###   {"error":"authorization_pending"}
### After approval, response contains access_token and this script saves {{accessToken}}.
# @name pollToken
POST {{brokerUrl}}/oauth2/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
Accept: application/json

grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:device_code&device_code={{deviceCode}}&client_id={{clientId}}&client_secret={{clientSecret}}

> {%
  if (response.body.access_token) {
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.access_token);
    client.log("access_token saved to {{accessToken}}");
  } else {
    client.log("No access token yet. error=" + (response.body.error || "unknown"));
  }
%}


### 6) Protected Call With Bearer Token
### Requires a successful Step 5 that saved {{accessToken}}.
GET {{protectedApiUrl}}/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: application/json
